import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['count'], bins=30, color='blue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['count'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['count'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Flight Counts')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight counts across all airports?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    grouped_data = data.groupby('origin')['count'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False)
    ax = grouped_data.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(15, 6), color='blue')
    max_origin = grouped_data.idxmax()
    max_count = grouped_data.max()
    plt.axhline(y=max_count, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Max: {max_count:.2f}')
    plt.title('Which airport has the highest number of flights departing from it?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Origin Airport')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Group by origin and sum the count
    grouped_data = data.groupby('origin')['count'].sum().reset_index()
    
    # Sort by count and get top 10 busiest airports
    top_10_airports = grouped_data.sort_values('count', ascending=False).head(10)
    
    # Filter data for top 10 busiest airports
    top_10_data = data[data['origin'].isin(top_10_airports['origin'])]
    
    # Create box plot
    ax = top_10_data.boxplot(column='count', by='origin', grid=False)
    
    # Set title and labels
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight counts for the top 10 busiest airports?')
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.xlabel('Origin')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Filter the least busy airports
    least_busy_airports = data.groupby('origin')['count'].sum().nsmallest(10).index

    # Filter the data for the least busy airports
    least_busy_data = data[data['origin'].isin(least_busy_airports)]

    # Create the box plot
    ax = least_busy_data.boxplot(column='count', by='origin', grid=False)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of flight counts for the least busy airports?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Origin')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    plt.suptitle('')

    # Add a horizontal line for the median value
    median_value = least_busy_data['count'].median()
    ax.axhline(y=median_value, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {median_value:.2f}')
    ax.legend()

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    grouped_data = data.groupby(['origin', 'destination']).sum().reset_index()
    grouped_data = grouped_data.sort_values('count', ascending=False).groupby('origin').head(1)
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    grouped_data.plot(kind='bar', x='origin', y='count', ax=ax, legend=False)
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_xlabel('Origin Airport')
    ax.set_title('Most Common Destination for Flights Departing from a Particular Airport')
    
    for i, row in grouped_data.iterrows():
        ax.text(i, row['count'], row['destination'], ha='center', va='bottom')
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
